</exercise><exercise id="eip-785"><problem id="eip-824">
  <para id="eip-314">
    Seeing patterns means that a sociologist needs to be able to:
<list id="eip-306" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item>compare the behavior of individuals from different societies</item>
    <item>compare one society to another</item>
    <item>identify similarities in how social groups respond to social pressure</item>
    <item>compare individuals to groups</item></list></para>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-985">
